results.name: Expansion of q^(1/4) * (eta(q^8) * eta(q^10) - eta(q^2) * eta(q^40)) / (eta(q^4) * eta(q^20)) in powers of q.
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000
formula: Denoted by "(160~a)" in Simon Norton's replicable function list.
G.f. is a period 1 Fourier series which satisfies f(-1 / (1280 t)) = f(t) where q = exp(2 Pi i t).
mathematica: QP = QPochhammer; s = (QP[q^8]*QP[q^10]-q*QP[q^2]*QP[q^40])/(QP[q^4]* QP[q^20]) + O[q]^90; CoefficientList[s, q] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Nov 30 2015, adapted from PARI *)
program: (PARI) {a(n) = local(A); if( n<0, 0, A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( (eta(x^8 + A) * eta(x^10 + A) - x * eta(x^2 + A) * eta(x^40 + A)) / (eta(x^4 + A) * eta(x^20 + A)), n))}
